# Axis 1 — one-shot resume

A handler that resumes its continuation exactly once. This is the minimal
control-interoperability capability: the portable-VM must suspend at the
`perform` site and resume with a supplied value. Reference-row baseline.

```scalascript
effect Ask:
  def ask(): Int

def prog(): Int =
  val x = Ask.ask()
  x + 1

val r = handle(prog()) {
  case Ask.ask(resume) => resume(41)
  case Return(x) => x
}
println(r)
```
